<subSubSection pageId="124" pageNumber="882" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="124.[787,1379,961,1385]" lastBlockId="124.[173,1380,1391,2174]" pageId="124" pageNumber="882">
Recent molecular studies based on mtDNA and nDNA showed genetic differences between North American and South American populations of 
<taxonomicName authority="P. Gervais, 1856" box="[1165,1249,1194,1227]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="124" pageNumber="882" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ega">L. ega</taxonomicName>
, suggest ing they are distinct species. Nevertheless, any taxonomic change was discarded, and broader analysis of subspecies is needed. 
<taxonomicName authority="P. Gervais, 1856" box="[789,961,1352,1385]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="124" pageNumber="882" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ega">Lasiurus ega</taxonomicName>
1s in the Yellow Bat group. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
